  }, "Commercial Application / Consideration / Ecosystem notes"), mdx("p", null, "Presently, there is no software designed for the \u2018webizen platform\u2019 as such, foundation partners (/early Adopters) are expected to be; either, groups who have advanced software development skills in-house or end-customers who employ the services of software developers (value added resellers); to produce new software, to deliver capabilities that are otherwise not available for deployment to one or more sites.\xA0 Whilst other solutions will seek to attend to other parts of the market, which is expected to develop overtime; these initial solutions are targeting end-user contract values that would start commercially at around $250,000 AUD and grow from there.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "Academic Pricing / support is going to be a major part of the go to market solutions. Academic institutions will be encouraged to purchase Webizen Platform solutions, at a significantly reduced rate.\xA0 The Hardware Form-factor can be provided with or without UPS and other peripheries; in a Rack Mountable or Free-Standing Enclosure.\xA0 Work is being performed also, to better understand how to support various environmental considerations ie: heat & noise; with a preference for resourcing a method to have an option that operates near silently.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The Webizen Platform intends to deliver tooling that enables networking between webizen devices (in particular); as to support processing tasks across federated systems, by design.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "These features are intended to incorporate various considerations; relating to security, networking of tasks / processes and in-turn also socio-economic & environmental \u2018currencies\u2019; which provides support for new features to be built into software & related applications.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The Primary Marketing Strategy is to support VARs who will in-turn on-sell Webizen-pro based solutions to high-end customers, who will require software developed for their specific needs."), mdx("p", null, "Overtime, webizen software will develop and the cost of ownership for entry-level solutions is expected to reduce; whilst the development of technology in the area, is expected to lead to continual capability growth due to the rapid development of more advanced hardware solutions."), mdx("p", null, "The commercial concept, in many circumstances, is expected to be similar to vehicle sales and after-sales service.\xA0 Webizen Customers are expected to require a service agreement; that will support maintenance of webizen systems and in-turn also, technical support when needed from Authorised\xA0 Webizen Experts; who will be subject to a variety of checks to ensure valid protections for webizen pro owners; and in-turn, subject to various forms of hygiene processes.."), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "the-software-environment"
  }, "The Software Environment:"), mdx("p", null, "The software environment is built upon Linux, with specific webizen software produced to make APIs available for the local software application environment; making use of virtualisation, HTML5 (inc. Javascript / NodeJS) and Python (in particular); alongside webizen AI fabric technology to provide a software development environment for value added resellers (VARs).\xA0\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "This new type of \u2018operating system\u2019 needs to be built.\xA0 There are many parts that have been constructed; however, they have not been assembled in a manner that can only be done if there\u2019s a hardware solution to build this particular type of \u2018operating system\u2019 to function on; and in-turn, power apps that have been built to be installed on those systems.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "In terms of defining the intended meaning of \u2018operating system\u2019, this is in-turn a future \u2018marketing\u2019 / communications task; to process, alongside the various others that exist.\xA0\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The Webizen Platform is not simply a computer \u2018operating system\u2019, nor is it simply a \u2018network based\u2019 operating system; nor is it simply an \u2018artificial intelligence\u2019 operating system; nonetheless, for now, I'm terming it an AiOS or Webizen AiOS.\xA0"), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "webizen-software-platform"
  }, "Webizen Software Platform"), mdx("p", null, "The thing that makes this all work, is the software platform. Not all \u2018apps\u2019 are expected to make use or require the hardware specifications provided by the \u201CWebizen Pro\u201D solutions; and some clients may elect to use hardware capabilities that are made available via the webizen secure inter-networking protocols.\xA0"), mdx("p", null, "The Webizen Platform is intended to provide a software environment that is owned by the entity operating it; and in-turn, provide support for contractual and/or moral relationships, between users or \u2018legal entities\u2019."), mdx("p", null, "In-effect, the systems are intended to support a meaningful relationship between the artefacts persons create in life; whilst doing work, recreation or rest (sleep) activities; and the moral \u2018ownership\u2019 of those artefacts.\xA0 This gets complicated when taking into account 3rd party statements / claims, alongside contractual relationships (moral, societal and socio-economic) associated with activity related artefacts."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "functionality-design-overview"
  }, "Functionality Design Overview"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Confidential Computing - Network Based: The Webizen pro ecosystem is designed to provide a self-hosted (\u201Con-prem\u201D) hardware/software solution that is operated via client devices as a federated cloud.\xA0 The Webizen pro uses Webizen software to support AI coupled activities. The Architecture supports isolation between cores; so that they can be assigned to different actors, and the software environment is migratable.  ", "Webizen Pro is designed to support federated activities between webizen enabled environments."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Webizen-Pro VPS: The Webizen Pro environment provides VPS hosting, for various types of \u2018hosting\u2019 packages.\xA0 In-effect, its a linux based hosting environment; with specialised functionality that provides unique capabilities, that can only be made most useful via software that is designed to make use of those features.\xA0\xA0"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "AiOs-DB: The Webizen Pro Software Stack, produces an integrated entity centric graph (SemWeb Based) database environment; built around traditional semantic web related technologies.  ", "This database environment is able to harmonise the data-formats between different RDBMS & Web2 APIs; as to provide an ACL controlled \u2018structured data harmonisation\u2019 layers between native \u2018applications\u2019, and others that may use MySQL or other RDBMS database platforms, alongside property-graph solutions (ie: GraphQL based).."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "AiOs-ML/DL: The Webizen Pro Software Stack supports distributed \u2018jobs\u2019.  ", "Data Processing is able to be performed in a distributed manner whilst maintaining confidentiality.\xA0 This is in-turn coupled to Webizen Currencies to support ESG related economics across webizen networked devices, to support the performance of shared cooperative and/or collaborative task processing requirements.\xA0"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Permissive Commons: The Webizen (pro) Software Stack supports \u201CPermissive Commons\u201D which provides artefacts required by AI for Confidential Computing and a variety of other useful applications.")), mdx("h4", {
    "id": "software-development-strategy"
  }, "Software Development Strategy"), mdx("p", null, "The software environment specifications are under active development.\xA0 Whilst there are an array of historical works that aids to inform what this looks like, generally, it isn\u2019t \u2018up-to-date\u2019.\xA0 In-turn, there are two primary development pathways associated with the development of webizen.\xA0 The first, is to make use of; and modify, existing components that are able to run on existing \u2013 modern - consumer level devices.\xA0 The second, is about engineering the webizen platform to realise the intended purpose / potential of the platform; which in-turn benefits from the insights gained through producing Apps & Tools using existing libraries. \xA0 The greatest capabilities brought about by the Webizen platform are AI based libraries that are designed to operate in a particular way; so that works produced are able to remain private when required."), mdx("h2", {
